# /api-review — API Review

## Usage
```
/api-review [target]
```

## Phases

### Phase 0 — Reconnaissance
1. Read endpoints, schemas, and services of the target
2. Check existing API contracts
3. Read rules in `.claude/rules/`

### Phase 1 — Review

#### 1. RESTful Compliance
- [ ] Correct HTTP verbs (GET=read, POST=create, PUT=replace, PATCH=partial, DELETE=remove)
- [ ] Semantic status codes (200, 201, 204, 400, 401, 403, 404, 409, 422, 500)
- [ ] URIs as plural nouns (`/users`, not `/getUsers`)
- [ ] API versioning (`/api/v1/`)
- [ ] Pagination on lists (`?page=1&limit=20`)

#### 2. Schemas & Validation
- [ ] Strict request schema validation
- [ ] Documented response schemas
- [ ] Consistent types (don't mix string/number)
- [ ] Clear optional vs required fields
- [ ] Validated enums

#### 3. Security
- [ ] Authentication verified on protected endpoints
- [ ] Authorization (roles/permissions) applied
- [ ] Input sanitized against injection
- [ ] Rate limiting considered
- [ ] Sensitive data not exposed in responses

#### 4. Performance
- [ ] Pagination on large lists
- [ ] Selectable fields (sparse fieldsets) if needed
- [ ] Cache headers configured
- [ ] N+1 queries avoided
- [ ] Compact payloads

#### 5. Error Handling
- [ ] Consistent error format
- [ ] Useful messages for consumers
- [ ] Stack traces NOT exposed in production
- [ ] Validation errors with per-field details

## Output Format

```markdown
# API Review — {target}

| Category | Score | Issues |
|----------|-------|--------|
| REST | X/10 | N |
| Schemas | X/10 | N |
| Security | X/10 | N |
| Performance | X/10 | N |
| Errors | X/10 | N |

## Critical Issues
1. ...

## Recommendations
1. ...

## Overall Score: X/10
```
